 1996, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1927, \"end\": 1938, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint_Lucia\", \"score\": 0.9999999998303792, \"rank\": 1.6967416270478893e-10, \"text\": \"Saint Lucia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint_Lucia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint_Lucia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I have seen Femke Bol win Olympic gold live.\", \"from\": 1998, \"to\": 2042, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2010, \"end\": 2019, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Femke_Bol\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Femke Bol\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Femke_Bol\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Femke_Bol\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"One of only 80,000 out of a population of 8.1bn.\", \"from\": 2043, \"to\": 2091, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"That last leg.\", \"from\": 2092, \"to\": 2106, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Insane.\", \"from\": 2107, \"to\": 2114, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Team GB's Daryll Neita is the only Brit who has made it through to the final.\", \"from\": 2116, \"to\": 2193, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2116, \"end\": 2123, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.924796888552438e-15, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}, {\"begin\": 2126, \"end\": 2138, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daryll_Neita\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Daryll Neita\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daryll_Neita\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daryll_Neita\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Neitashould be in with a good chance of success here as she achieved the fourth-fastest time across the eight semis.\", \"from\": 2195, \"to\": 2311, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It's absolutely electric in the Stade de France, as they roar Femke Bol past the Americans, who look genuinely gutted to have won silver.\", \"from\": 2313, \"to\": 2450, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2375, \"end\": 2384, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Femke_Bol\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Femke Bol\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Femke_Bol\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Femke_Bol\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A brilliant bronze for the Brits though.\", \"from\": 2452, \"to\": 2492, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Amber Anning subbed in for the final and ran the second-fastest final leg of any team.\", \"from\": 2493, \"to\": 2579, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She almost ran down her University of Arkansas team-mate Kaylyn Brown in the final metres, but the Americans hung on by 0.27 seconds.\", \"from\": 2580, \"to\": 2713, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A great run from Team GB - but the big shock is Femke Bol of the Netherlands overtaking the US at the death to take gold.\", \"from\": 2715, \"to\": 2836, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2780, \"end\": 2791, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\", \"score\": 0.667100799822505, \"rank\": 0.4990211389096374, \"text\": \"Netherlands\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\"}, {\"begin\": 2807, \"end\": 2809, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9996331706168582, \"rank\": 0.00036675330649092557, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Wow.\", \"from\": 2837, \"to\": 2841, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Team GB's fifth bronze of the day.\", \"from\": 2843, \"to\": 2877, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2843, \"end\": 2850, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.924796888552438e-15, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"800m to go - the USA are in the lead but Team GB chasing.\", \"from\": 2879, \"to\": 2936, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2896, \"end\": 2899, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"score\": 0.9998846286294946, \"rank\": 0.00011536382376272246, \"text\": \"USA\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_women's_national_soccer_team\"}, {\"begin\": 2920, \"end\": 2927, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.924796888552438e-15, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Team GB were strong in the heats and should have a decent medal chance here.\", \"from\": 2938, \"to\": 3014, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The mixed 4x400m relay has just begun at the Stade de France - Samuel Reardon, Laviai Nielsen, Alex Haydock-Wilson and Amber Anning the four British runners.\", \"from\": 3016, \"to\": 3173, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3095, \"end\": 3109, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Laviai_Nielsen\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Laviai Nielsen\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Laviai_Nielsen\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Laviai_Nielsen\"}, {\"begin\": 3111, \"end\": 3115, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_Rousseau\", \"score\": 0.9999999609303821, \"rank\": 3.8614943002255e-08, \"text\": \"Alex\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_Rousseau\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_Rousseau\"}, {\"begin\": 3157, \"end\": 3164, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"score\": 0.9986638079611071, \"rank\": 0.0008163954482322404, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I am a woman.\", \"from\": 3175, \"to\": 3188, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The words of Imane Khelif herself, spoken with passion and sincerity inthe most trying of circumstances.\", \"from\": 3189, \"to\": 3293, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Whatever the rights and wrongs ofthe gender controversy that has engulfed her at these Olympic Games, or whatever others might say about her, she is unequivocal in this belief.\", \"from\": 3295, \"to\": 3471, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Despite the provocation, she has behaved with dignity throughout the storm, none of which is of her making.\", \"from\": 3473, \"to\": 3580, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Read Kevin's full analysis of Khelif's fighthere  Farcical scenes at the shot put, the athletes are slipping all over the place after the rain has fallen.\", \"from\": 3582, \"to\": 3736, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Nigeria's Chukuwuebuka Enekwechi ended up on his backside.\", \"from\": 3738, \"to\": 3796, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3738, \"end\": 3745, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nigeria_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9994089510876197, \"rank\": 0.0005816353633964794, \"text\": \"Nigeria\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nigeria_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nigeria_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Sam Reardon is one of the four Brits lining up in the mixed 4x400m relay final shortly.\", \"from\": 3798, \"to\": 3885, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3798, \"end\": 3801, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sam_Winchester\", \"score\": 0.9978952307474175, \"rank\": 0.002109208424336157, \"text\": \"Sam\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sam_Winchester\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sam_Winchester\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This is his fascinating story after he lost his 'biggest support and best friend' in 2019.\", \"from\": 3887, \"to\": 3977, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Read James' interview with Samhere.\", \"from\": 3979, \"to\": 4014, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Having swam in the heats, he is out of the 4x100m relay final which gets going just before 9pm.\", \"from\": 4016, \"to\": 4111, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Kathleen Dawson, James Wilby, Anna Hopkin and Duncan Scott will be the Team GB lineup as they take on the favourites USA and Leon Marchand's French team.\", \"from\": 4113, \"to\": 4266, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4113, \"end\": 4128, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kathleen_Dawson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kathleen Dawson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kathleen_Dawson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kathleen_Dawson\"}, {\"begin\": 4130, \"end\": 4141, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Wilby\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.569158183257779e-16, \"text\": \"James Wilby\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Wilby\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Wilby\"}, {\"begin\": 4143, \"end\": 4154, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anna_Hopkin\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Anna Hopkin\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anna_Hopkin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/reso